#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:134
msgid "Plugin operation description"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:136
msgid "The \"Return Requests WooCommerce\" plugin allows customers to submit order return requests in the online store. Guest users can use a form followed by email verification, while logged-in customers can submit returns directly from the \"My Account\" panel. The plugin generates a PDF file with return information and emails it to both the store administrator and the customer. Optional Cloudflare Turnstile protection is implemented to prevent SPAM."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:141
msgid "Required plugins"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:145
msgid "Required for managing orders and customers."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:151
msgid "Support Return Requests"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:153
msgid "I created Return Requests to give the WordPress community a truly free, native, and bloat-free return management solution. If this plugin saves you time or money, please consider buying me a coffee! It directly helps me maintain the project and develop new features."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:156
msgid "Buy me a coffee"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:165
msgid "This plugin provides a comprehensive native return management workflow for WooCommerce, securely handling returns from both authenticated users and guests."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:169
msgid "1. Configuration and Initialization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:171
msgid "System Status"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:171
msgid "You can disable the system using the toggle in the Information tab while you configure the plugin, and re-enable it when you are ready to launch."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:173
msgid "Automated Pages"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:173
msgid "By clicking \"Check and Create Required Pages\" in the Pages tab, three routing pages are automatically created using shortcodes (Return Form, Select Return Items, Return Confirmation)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:174
msgid "Tip: These automatically created pages are fully customizable. The generated shortcode must remain on the page, but you can add your own content below or above it as needed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:176
msgid "In the Law Compliance tab, you can select your store's legal region to automatically display the correct consumer protection act disclaimer during the return process. You can also write your own custom legal disclaimer."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:179
msgid "Localization & Translation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:181
msgid "This plugin is fully translatable on both the frontend and backend. English is the default base language, but Polish (pl_PL) is 100% pre-built out-of-the-box. The plugin automatically grabs your active WordPress language setting to display the proper language if translations exist. Missing translations can be easily added using standard translation plugins like Open World or Loco Translate."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:184
msgid "2. The Flow for Logged-In Customers"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:186
msgid "A logged-in user visits their \"My Account\" dashboard and navigates to \"Orders\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:187
msgid "If an order has the status \"Completed\" and falls within the statutory return window, a \"Return\" button natively appears next to the order."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:188
msgid "Once clicked, the plugin generates a secure session token directly on the server without needing an email verification step (since the user identity is already verified by WordPress)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:189
msgid "The user is instantly redirected to the Select Return Items page with their authenticated session active."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:192
msgid "3. The Flow for Guest Customers (Unregistered)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:194
msgid "A guest user visits the Return Form page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:195
msgid "They input their Order Number and the Billing Email Address associated with that order."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:196
msgid "The plugin cross-references the database and generates a cryptographically secure 1-hour Return Token tying their request to that specific order."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:197
msgid "An automated email is dispatched to the user containing a one-time verification link."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:198
msgid "Upon clicking the link, the user's browser establishes an authenticated system session using the token, proving they own the email address. They are then securely redirected to the Select Return Items page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:201
msgid "4. Form Submission and PDF Generation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:203
msgid "Once the user reaches the Select Return Items page, they select the exact items they wish to return and input their bank account number."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:204
msgid "Optionally, a Cloudflare Turnstile gateway protects the form from automated abuse."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:205
msgid "Upon clicking \"Return Selected Items\", the request is officially recorded in the custom database table."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:206
msgid "The generative engine constructs a Goods Return Protocol PDF, filling it automatically with the store's details, the customer's billing address, and a compliance declaration."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:207
msgid "The PDF is saved securely to the server."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:208
msgid "Two automated emails are dispatched: A confirmation to the Customer including the attached PDF, and a notification to the Administrator containing the same attached PDF."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:209
msgid "The customer's secure session is flushed and they land on the final Confirmation page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:212
msgid "5. Email Notifications Overview"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:214
msgid "Verification Email (Guest only):"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:214
msgid "Sent immediately after a guest submits the initial Return Form to verify their identity via a secure link. E-mail in form needs to match order billing e-mail."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:215
msgid "Customer Confirmation:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:215
msgid "Sent after successfully selecting items and generating the Return Protocol PDF. Contains the PDF as an attachment."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:216
msgid "Administrator Notification:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:216
msgid "Sent simultaneously to the store owner alerting them of the return, with the Return Protocol PDF attached."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:219
msgid "6. Return Status Management and Order Integration"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:221
msgid "Return List Backend:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:221
msgid "All returns arrive with a \"Pending\" status in the main plugin table. Administrators can use quick action buttons to mark a return as \"Completed\" or flag it as an \"Issue\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:222
msgid "WooCommerce Order Meta Box:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:222
msgid "When viewing a specific order from the WooCommerce interface, a dedicated Meta Box will surface the associated Return. Store owners can alter the status from here natively."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:223
msgid "Issue Resolution Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin-pages/main-page.php:223
msgid "If a return is flagged as an \"Issue\" through the Order Meta Box, an optional explanation box appears. Submitting an explanation dynamically saves it as a Customer Order Note, updating the buyer automatically via WooCommerce's built-in email alerts."
msgstr ""

